today, and again we can use our

00:32:34.486 --> 00:32:38.807
jargon.
Definition- Player i's

00:32:38.807 --> 00:32:48.697
strategy, "s'_i" is
weakly dominated by her strategy

00:32:48.697 --> 00:32:58.263
"s_i" if--now we're
going to take advantage of our

00:32:58.263 --> 00:33:07.829
notation--if Player i's payoff
from choosing "s_i"

00:33:07.829 --> 00:33:17.720
against "s_-i" is
always as big as or equal,

00:33:17.720 --> 00:33:22.328
to her payoff from choosing
"s'_i" against

00:33:22.328 --> 00:33:27.660
"s_-i" and this has to
be true for all things that

00:33:27.660 --> 00:33:31.328
anyone else could do.
And in addition,

00:33:31.328 --> 00:33:36.080
Player i's payoff from choosing
"s_i" against

00:33:36.080 --> 00:33:40.921
"s_-i" is strictly
better than her payoff from

00:33:40.921 --> 00:33:45.849
choosing "s'_i"
against "s_-i,"

00:33:45.849 --> 00:33:50.529
for at least one thing that
everyone else could do.

00:33:50.529 --> 00:33:54.335
Just check, that exactly
corresponds to the easy and hard

00:33:54.335 --> 00:33:57.332
